r于1490年出生在德国巴登-爾特波格斯圖特加特莫林根。她于1540年与Andreas Hans Schuhmacher在德国巴登-爾特波格结婚。他们至少是1个女儿的父母。她去世于1540年在她的家乡享年50岁。"},"hr":{"1490–1540":"1490.–1540.","1490–1545":"1490.–1545","1470–1545":"1470–1545","1520–1584":"1520.–1584","1545":"1545","1520":"1520.","1540":"1540.","1584":"1584","1470":"1470","1490":"1490.","Württemberg-Hohenzollern, Germany":"Baden-Württemberg, Njemačka","Moehringen, Neckarkreis, Baden-Wuerttemberg, Germany":"Möhringen, Stuttgart, Baden-Württemberg, Njemačka","Möhringen, Stuttgart, Württemberg, Deutschland":"Möhringen, Oberamt Stuttgart, Württemberg, Njemačka"},"cs":{"1490–1540":"1490–1540","1490–1545":"1490–1545","1470–1545":"1470–1545","1520–1584":"1520–1584","1545":"1545","1520":"1520","1540":"1540","1584":"1584","1470":"1470","1490":"1490","Württemberg-Hohenzollern, Germany":"Baden-Württemberg, Německo","Moehringen, Neckarkreis, Baden-Wuerttemberg, Germany":"Möhringen, Stuttgart, Baden-Württemberg, Německo","Möhringen, Stuttgart, Württemberg, Deutschland":"Möhringen, Oberamt Stuttgart, Württemberg, Německo"},"da":{"1490–1540":"1490–1540","1490–1545":"1490–1545","1470–1545":"1470–1545","1520–1584":"1520–1584","1545":"1545","1520":"1520","1540":"1540","1584":"1584","1470":"1470","1490":"1490","Württemberg-Hohenzollern, Germany":"Baden-Württemberg, Tyskland","Moehringen, Neckarkreis, Baden-Wuerttemberg, Germany":"Möhringen, Stuttgart, Baden-Württemberg, Tyskland","Möhringen, Stuttgart, Württemberg, Deutschland":"Möhringen, Oberamt Stuttgart, Württemberg, Tyskland"},"nl":{"1490–1540":"1490–1540","1490–1545":"1490–1545","1470–1545":"1470–1545","1520–1584":"1520–1584","1545":"1545","1520":"1520","1540":"1540","1584":"1584","1470":"1470","1490":"1490","Württemberg-Hohenzollern, Germany":"Baden-Württemberg, Duitsland","Moehringen, Neckarkreis, Baden-Wuerttemberg, Germany":"Möhringen, Stuttgart, Baden-Württemberg, Duitsland","Möhringen, Stuttgart, Württemberg, Deutschland":"Möhringen, Oberamt Stuttgart, Württemberg, Duitsland"},"en":{"1490–1540":"1490–1540","1490–1545":"1490–1545","1470–1545":"1470–1545","1520–1584":"1520–1584","1545":"1545","1520":"1520","1540":"1540","1584":"1584","1470":"1470","1490":"1490","Württemberg-Hohenzollern, Germany":"Baden-Württemberg, Germany","Moehringen, Neckarkreis, Baden-Wuerttemberg, Germany":"Möhringen, Stuttgart, Baden-Württemberg, Germany","Möhringen, Stuttgart, Württemberg, Deutschland":"Möhringen, Stuttgart, Württemberg, Germany","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Ziegler","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["German and Jewish (Ashkenazic): occupational name for a tiler, from an agent derivative of Middle High German <i>ziegel</i> ‘roof tile’ (Old High German <i>ziagal</i>, from Latin <i>tegula</i>), German <i>Ziegel</i>. In the Middle Ages the term came to denote bricks as well as tiles, and so the name <i>Ziegler</i> may have also denoted a brickmaker or bricklayer (compare 2 below). This surname is also found in France (Alsace and Lorraine), Denmark, Poland, Czechia, and Hungary. Compare   Zeagler  ,   Zeigler  , and   Zigler  .","In some cases also a Germanized form of Slovenian   Cigler   or of its variant <b>Ciglar</b> ‘brickmaker’, cognates of 1 above.","History: The surname <i>Ziegler</i> was probably first brought to North America in the early 18th century by Michael Ziegler from Germany, who settled in what is now Montgomery County, PA. The town of Zieglerville, PA, is named after him. Michael Ziegler was Lutheran, but converted to the Mennonite faith. Today the name Ziegler is also found among the Brethrens."],"variants":[{"name":"Sigler","meanings":["German: occupational name for a maker of seals and signet rings, or for an official keeper of a seal, from an agent derivative of Middle High German <i>sigel</i> ‘seal’.","Probably also an Americanized form of German   Ziegler  ."]},{"name":"Zeigler","meanings":["Altered form of German   Ziegler   ‘tiler, brickmaker’."]},{"name":"Ziegel","meanings":["German and Jewish (Ashkenazic): metonymic occupational name for a tiler or tile maker or a roofer, from Middle High German <i>ziegel</i>, German <i>Ziegel</i> ‘roof tile’ (see   Ziegler  )."]},{"name":"Zeagler","meanings":["Americanized form of German   Ziegler   ‘tiler, brickmaker’."]},{"name":"Ziegelbauer","meanings":["German: occupational name for a tiler, from <i>Ziegel</i> ‘roof tile’ (see   Ziegler  ) + <i>Bauer</i> (see   Bauer  )."]},{"name":"Ziglar","meanings":["Altered form of German   Ziegler  ."]},{"name":"Zigler","meanings":["German and Jewish (Ashkenazic): variant of   Ziegler   ‘tiler, brickmaker’ and, in North America, (also) an altered form of this. This surname is rare in Germany."]}]},{"name":"Katharina","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From Greek.  See  <b>Katherine</b> ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Katharina Ziegler was born in 1490, in Möhringen, Stuttgart, Baden-Württemberg, Germany. She married Andreas Hans Schuhmacher in 1540, in Baden-Württemberg, Germany. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died in 1540, in her hometown, at the age of 50."},"et":{"1490–1540":"1490–1540","1490–1545":"1490–1545","1470–1545":"1470–1545","1520–1584":"1520–1584","1545":"1545","1520":"1520","1540":"1540","1584":"1584","1470":"1470","1490":"1490","Württemberg-Hohenzollern, Germany":"Baden-Württemberg, Saksamaa","Moehringen, Neckarkreis, Baden-Wuerttemberg, Germany":"Möhringen, Stuttgart, Baden-Württemberg, Saksamaa","Möhringen, Stuttgart, Württemberg, Deutschland":"Möhringen, Oberamt Stuttgart, Württemberg, Saksamaa"},"fi":{"1490–1540":"1490–1540","1490–1545":"1490–1545","1470–1545":"1470–1545","1520–1584":"1520–1584","1545":"1545","1520":"1520","1540":"1540","1584":"1584","1470":"1470","1490":"1490","Württemberg-Hohenzollern, Germany":"Baden-Württemberg, Saksa","Moehringen, Neckarkreis, Baden-Wuerttemberg, Germany":"Möhringen, Stuttgart, Baden-Württemberg, Saksa","Möhr